properties.Name: Amazon Warehouse
properties.description: 2801 S Western Ave;  Amazon is reorganizing to expand its distribution operations into urban warehousing districts areas.  This is the second such warehouse in Chicago , after the facility on Goose Island.

properties.Name: Domino Foods Corp
properties.description: 2905 S Western Ave; the Distribution Center for Domino Sugar Corp; receipt by barge of sugar products. Domino Sugar is part of ASR group, the largest vertically-integrated sugar refiner in the world (growing, milling, refining, and distribution). Production capacity is more than six million tonnes of sugar annually. The ASR group was formed in the 1998 the merger of two Florida sugar giants and now operates in the Americas, Caribbean, Europe, the Middle East, India and Asia.

properties.Name: SpaceNet
properties.description: 3111 S Western Ave.  Network security and satellite services for government, Oil and Gas, utilities customers as well as federal, state and local public safety agencies; terrestrial, mobile and satellite technologies; a subsidiary of SageNet based out of Tulsa, OK

properties.Name: Bell Oil Terminal
properties.description: Asphalt and residual oil by barge;  oil and asphalt pipelines connect to storage tanks; serviced by rail

properties.Name: Fed Ex
properties.description: 1901 W Chicago Ave and 3000 S Damen Ave. 41-acre vacant site bisected by the Damen Ave. FedEx Ground complex: eastern portion to include distribution building with 120 loading docks and 8,000-sq. ft. of office space. The western portion to include a 6.9-acre truck yard and a 450-space parking lot.

properties.Name: Ameropan Oil
properties.description: 3301 S California Ave. Distilate, residual and other fuel oils; petroleum pitches, coke, asphalt, naphta and solvents. Receives slurry oil by barge from Exxon Mobile in Lemont; slurry oil is a byproduct of refining heavy crude (from the refinery fluid catalytic cracking unit); it is called by many names, essentially what remains after the “high-value “ material is removed from the crude. Either used locally as a cheap boiler fuel for industrial applications, as feed stock for carbon black, or transported by barge to New Orleans and shipped to Latin America as a cheap fuel. 0.7 gallons is generated for each barrel of heavy crude oil.

properties.Name: Prairie Materials Yard #33
properties.description: Ready-Mix Concrete Plant - 3300 S California Ave. Doubled its capacity with the addition of a second concrete plant this August in the adjacent property. Part of Votoratim Cimientos which operates in 14 countries. Also added 2 liquid nitrogen cooling stations last June for on-site pours. Truck/barge/rail connectivity. Prairie Materials also distribute aggregates through a global network of quarries, pits, depots, and ready-mixed yards.

properties.Name: Cook County Jail
properties.description: How are prisons and jails environmentally toxic to prisoners, communities and larger ecosystems? Can we speak of Cook County Jail as symptom and a form of economic, racial and ecological violence? What is at stake in new trends to make prisons and jails more green and sustainable?

properties.Name: Citgo Compound Plant and Wharf, Cicero
properties.description: Makes lubrication products; The largest producer of two-cycle engine oils in the United States, the Cicero plant has the storage capacity for more than one million gallons of packaged lubricant products; receipt of chemical inputs by barge; storage and distribution by rail and truck

properties.Name: Olympic Oil
properties.description: Receipt of petroleum products and ethylene glycol by barge, plus antifreeze storage. Olympic has a long-term lease from the Water Reclamation District and has a long history of spills into the canal.

properties.Name: Koppers Inc. Stickney PLant
properties.description: Coal is carbonized to make coke and Koppers purchases a by-product of Coke-Coal tar. Koppers distills the coal tar and manufactures carbon materials and chemicals for the aluminum, steel, paint, plastic, wood-preserving, and carbon black industries. This plant: converts various crude tars into liquid pitch and other liquid products (creosote, refined tars, chemical oils and coal tar pitch). The wharf: receipt and shipment of petroleum products, residual oils, carbon black oil, tar etc by barge.
